# scripts/.test-policy-allowlist
#
# Format: <rule> <path>:<line> <one-line reason>
#
# One entry per line. Comments start with `#`.
# See system-documents/TEST_STRATEGY.md § 5 for policy details.
#
# Rules:
#   P1 = todo!/unimplemented!/panic!("not implemented") in production code
#   P2 = // TODO / // FIXME in production code
#   P3 = test function with no assert!/expect/unwrap
#   P4 = #[ignore] without an "// allowlisted: <reason>" marker
#   P5 = tests/*.rs orphan (not assigned to a tier)
#   P6 = tests/*.rs with no #[test] functions
#
# When an allowlisted line moves, update the line number here. The scanner
# does not auto-track drift; leaving stale entries defeats the purpose.
